sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(Dashboard/SDK)
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Proxy as model-registry proxy<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (Istio mTLS)
    participant MySQL as MySQL Database<br/>3306/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as model-registry controller<br/>8081/TCP health
    participant CSI as CSI Storage Initializer
    participant S3 as External Storage<br/>(S3/GCS) 443/TCP
    participant Catalog as model-catalog<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant HF as HuggingFace API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,MySQL: Flow 1: Model Registration via REST API
    Client->>Gateway: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>Proxy: Forward (Istio mTLS)<br/>VirtualService: kubeflow-gateway
    Proxy->>MySQL: INSERT model metadata<br/>Auth: Username/Password<br/>Optional TLS 1.2+
    MySQL-->>Proxy: OK
    Proxy-->>Gateway: 201 Created (JSON)
    Gateway-->>Client: Response

    Note over K8sAPI,Controller: Flow 2: InferenceService Sync (Controller)
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch Event: InferenceService created/updated<br/>Auth: SA Token, TLS
    Controller->>Proxy: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/inference_services<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Optional Bearer Token
    Proxy->>MySQL: Store inference service state
    MySQL-->>Proxy: OK
    Proxy-->>Controller: 200 OK
    Controller->>K8sAPI: PATCH InferenceService labels<br/>Auth: SA Token, TLS

    Note over CSI,S3: Flow 3: Model Download via CSI Storage Initializer
    Note right of CSI: KServe injects CSI as init container
    CSI->>Proxy: GET model artifact location<br/>model-registry://model/version<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    Proxy->>MySQL: Lookup artifact URI
    MySQL-->>Proxy: s3://bucket/model-path
    Proxy-->>CSI: Artifact URI response
    CSI->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Provider-specific (IAM)
    S3-->>CSI: Model artifacts

    Note over Catalog,PG: Flow 4: Catalog Source Synchronization
    Catalog->>HF: GET model metadata<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: API Key (optional)
    HF-->>Catalog: Model metadata response
    Catalog->>PG: Store catalog entries<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    PG-->>Catalog: OK
    Client->>Catalog: GET /api/model_catalog/v1alpha1/models<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP (Istio mTLS)
    Catalog-->>Client: Catalog search results
